<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 3:42PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southeastern Appomattox and northern Charlotte Counties through 415
PM EDT...
At 342 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Madisonville, or near Red House, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Red House...
Pamplin City...
Madisonville...
Abilene...
Cullen...
Hixburg...
and Evergreen.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
